Dev Guide (Nem):
to run serial version 
>wsl
>make 
>./serial

to run Open MP version
>wsl
>gcc -o rocket_openmp rocket_openmp.c rocket_physics.c rocket_utils.c -lm -fopenmp -O3
>./rocket_openmp 4

to run full comparison without CUDA
>wsl
>make compare
>mpirun -np 4 ./compare

or
>chmod +x run_compare_no_cuda.sh
>./run_compare_no_cuda.sh 4

to run full comparison with CUDA support
>wsl or HPC CUDA node
>make compare_cuda
>mpirun -np 4 ./compare_cuda

or
>chmod +x run_compare_cuda.sh
>./run_compare_cuda.sh 4

If CUDA is not available, use ./compare. If ./compare_cuda is built but the
computer has no CUDA GPU, the CUDA part is skipped automatically.

automatic option
>wsl or HPC node
>chmod +x run_compare.sh
>./run_compare.sh 4

This script builds and runs compare_cuda when nvcc is available. Otherwise it
builds and runs the normal compare program.
